James

Subject: Re: Submitting content for April E-Newsletter

Hi James,

Please find attached Dr Farhadieh’s Article.

If you need anything else, please let me know.

All the best,

Moriah

On 19 Mar 2018, at 4:55 PM, James Croll <JamesCroll@hssaustralia.com.au> wrote:

Thanks Moriah … here’s what to do …

· If Dr Farhadieh could write an article or item of news that he believes would be of interest to GP’s that would be great. In particular content that is likely to make the GP refer business to his practive

· Ideally, this should be topical and “newsworthy” .. ie: content based on recent research, findings, or developments that the GP is unlikely to have read or come across before.

That said, a recent feature he’s written for another publication is fine as long as we can publish with his approval.

· Length wise .. anything from 300 words to 1,000 words is fine

· We would like 2 or 3 supporting images as well.

· If the above could reach me by Friday, 30th March that would be great

First off .. can you let me know the subject matter he intends to submit?

The above should give him what he needs

Kind regards,

James Croll

Marketing and Events Manager
